<br>
My biggest problem with PoP, is the development of &quot;essential&quot; classes during Exp groups.<br>
<br>
Before PoP, the only true instances where concept of &quot;essential&quot; classes existed was during raids. As an example, Without X number of clerics, killing Emp in Ssra is basically impossible. This is fine in my mind, since &quot;Raids&quot; are meant to be done by a large balanced force.<br>
<br>
The problem that I see is, like I said, with Exp groups.<br>
<br>
Before PoP, a 6 Person Exp Group could consist of a large variety of classes. The success of the hunt usually depended upon the target choices that the group makes with the force available. For example, a group consisting of 5 mages and a Shaman can successfully kill Shrooms and Fungus Beasts in FG with little problem. An alternative group, with Warrior, Rogue, Enchanter, Cleric, Mage, Wizard can hunt &quot;Juggs&quot; in Seb and achieve equal or better experience efficiency as the aforementioned group.<br>
<br>
Since the introduction of PoP, where mobs easily hit for 400+, the same need for &quot;essential&quot; classes arise, not only for raids, but for the normal experience groups. If groups deviated from the optimal structure of:<br>
<br>
1) Warrior<br>
2) Cleric<br>
3) Enchanter<br>
4) Damage class<br>
5) Damage class<br>
6) Damage class<br>
<br>
then the experience efficiency of the group declines substantially.<br>
<br>
Having hunted in PoD, PoN, PoI, PoV, PoStorm, CoD, I find that there are rarely any locations where a &quot;slower&quot; of some type is not needed. If a slower were not available, then a Warrior is almost certainly needed to mitigate the higher damage received. An Enchanter is also very necessarily in most camps, since most mobs are &quot;linked&quot; and cannot easily be single pulled (especially since CoH is disabled in many zones). This leads to yet another &quot;essential&quot; class.<br>
<br>
Of course, these &quot;essential&quot; classes can be placed by others like Druids, SKs, Paladins, Monks, or Shaman. But it seems that the content available to this type of &quot;alternative&quot; group is sparse at level 61, and nearly non-existent at level 65.<br>
<br>
Perhaps you've all experienced what I have? Have you ever sat in a group of 5 people, but can't do anything substantial because you're waiting for the &quot;right&quot; class to fill that 6th spot?<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, I'm not wise enough to come up with any brilliant solutions. I guess I'm just saddened that while trying to force a social, grouping oriented game, SOE has consequently created two new categories of &quot;Essentials&quot; and &quot;Non-Essentials&quot;, further adding friction to a game that many of us attempt to draw satisfaction from.<br>
<br>
