<br>
I can't speak for groups without an Enchanter, since I am one, however:<br>
<br>
We did a group in PoV killing the fungusbeasts.  Group consisted of 2 Rangers, 1 Rogue, 1 Enchanter, 1 Shaman and 1 Cleric.<br>
<br>
Did geonids in PoV.  Group was Mage, 3 Rangers, Enchanter and Cleric.<br>
<br>
Did undead and larvae in PoV with a Druid healer.<br>
<br>
Guild group did consorts in PoN.  2 Monks, 1 Necromancer, 1 Bard, 1 Druid and 1 Cleric.<br>
<br>
Did spiders in PoD.  2 Mages, 1 Wizard, 1 Enchanter, 1 Ranger and 1 Cleric.<br>
<br>
We did a 2 group raid in PoStorms on Giants with a Ranger tanking.  We also did a 2 group raid on Koka`Vors in Storms with a Monk tanking.<br>
<br>
Yes, you need slowing, tanks, damage output, and healing in groups, but that's not really any different than it was before.  Shamans, Enchanters, Beastlords, and Bards can all slow.  Rangers with epics can too.  Clerics heal the best, but Druids and Shamans are quite good now with their heal upgrades as well.  And, believe it or not other classes besides Warriors can tank.  Monks and Rangers both have a good defensive discipline, and Paladins and Shadow Knights can do very nicely as well.<br>
<br>
I just think way too many people are stuck in the mindset that you can't go anywhere without the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>best</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of what you need.  Believe it or not, if you don't have the best tank or best slower, you can still make do with a Cleric.  If you have the best tank and slwoer, you can make do with a Druid or Shaman healer.  <br>
<br>
There are lots of alternatives besides the so-called &quot;holy trinity.&quot;  People just have to stop being afraid to try them. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.aol.com/nodnarbjh/csig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
