<br>
To summarize:<br>
<br>
Pre-PoP: No matter the composition of the group, the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Experience Efficiency</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>ANY</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> 6 person group is roughly the same. The only &quot;variable&quot; is the location of the hunt.<br>
<br>
Post-PoP: Because nearly <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>ALL</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> content has a minimum level of difficulty, the more you deviate from the &quot;Most efficient&quot; group (which is the list that I stated), the lower will be your <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Experience Efficiency</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
I'm well aware that there are many different options in how to form a 6 man group. While I'm not an EQ guru, I have experienced enough things to know that. To reiterate, when you have a less than optimum group, your <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Experience Efficiency</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> decreases so dramatically that some classes become &quot;Essential&quot;. That is my true problem with the way the game has evolved. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mitglied.lycos.de/sirnamib/hpbimg/xerph.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->[65 Arch Convoker] <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60465" target="top">Xerphanis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Officer of &lt; <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.monkeyo.org/enshadowed" target="top">Enshadowed</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> &gt;</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kaid2373>kaid2373</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#333333>(11/8/02 8:41:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=405.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://isaythere.solinus.com/swgwok_f_mb.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Groups</span><hr size=1> People are falling into that mentality but I have been having good luck with some very non standard groups. Pop does make a few things a bit more needed<br>
<br>
Tank you don't need a warrior but you do need somebody with a fair amount of hp. Warrior, pallies, and sk typically fill this spot but I have also gotten huge xp with a bard main tank surpisingly enough.<br>
<br>
Slower with mobs that hit this hard you need either a chanter or a shaman. Typically I prefer a shaman here as they an also heal quite good.<br>
<br>
Healer If you use a shaman slower this spot can be easily filled by another shaman or druid and if you use a chanter as slower you may want a cleric but it is not necessary.<br>
<br>
Anything else for other three slots pop depends more on people who know how to play their character than the types of classes. This expansion is not forgiving of people who make mistakes and those who really don't know there classes well tend to get dead in really horrific ways.<br>
<br>
Since pop opened my mage has gone from 56 to very nearly 58 and for as little as I play that is amazing. I have seen some instances of people searching for the perfect group and then having to disband due to not finding it while those left behind joined together and did fine for themselves. <br>
<br>
I myself am quite pleased with the balance of classes in pop mages are coming into our own as damage dealers and wanted as such. Paladins and Shadowknights now have valued position plate tanks are very hot commodities now in a way I didnt see as much previous to pop.  All damage dealing classes I have talked to are pretty happy as they all shine well against the hard hitting but not uber hp pop mobs.<br>
<br>
<br>
I think the biggest thing in pop is not to have the &quot;perfect&quot; group but to have a well balanced group with people who know how to play their classes.<br>
<br>
<br>
Kaid<br>
